# Notes:
# 1. Install Caddy: https://caddyserver.com/docs/install
# 2. Run: caddy run --config Caddyfile_websocket
# 3. Or as service: sudo systemctl start caddy
# 4. Caddy automatically handles HTTPS with Let's Encrypt (no manual cert setup!)
# 5. WebSocket upgrade is automatic (no special config needed unlike NGINX)
# 6. Logs: caddy logs are written to stderr by default
# 7. Reload config: caddy reload --config Caddyfile_websocket
